The paper deals with machine learning techniques for density estimation and imputation of missing data, which are topics that are commonly studied in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of optimization techniques and the modelling of correlations between variables suggest that the paper could also be relevant to the sub-field of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also deals with the handling of multidimensional data, which is a topic that is commonly studied in the sub-field of data science (cs.DS). Finally, the use of hierarchical modelling techniques suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the sub-field of social and information networks (cs.SI).
